	ckets\nResale Tickets \n50 First Jokes About America LIVE at Punch Line Ph
	illy\nGet ready for a hilarious patriotic comedy extravaganza as 50 First 
	Jokes About America takes the stage at Punch Line Philly in Philadelphia\,
	 PA on July 3\, 2026 — just in time for Independence Day weekend! This all
	-star comedy showcase celebrates America through the lens of stand-up come
	dy\, featuring a rotating lineup of top comedians delivering their best ma
	terial about life in the USA. \nEvent Details\nDate: Friday\, July 3\, 202
	6\nTime: 7:00 PM EDT\nVenue: Punch Line Philly\nAddress: 33 E. Laurel Stre
	et\, Philadelphia\, PA 19123\nAge Requirement: 21+ (18+ with parent or leg
	al guardian over 30)\nDrink Minimum: 2-beverage minimum per person \nAbout
	 50 First Jokes About America\n50 First Jokes About America is a special c
	omedy showcase celebrating the nation’s birthday weekend with 50 hilarious
	 jokes about American life\, culture\, and everything in between. Featurin
	g some of the best comedians in the country\, this show is the perfect way
	 to kick off your Fourth of July celebrations with laughter. Past editions
	 have featured comedians who have appeared on Comedy Central\, late-night 
	talk shows\, and major streaming platforms. \nWhat to Expect\n\nA high-ene
	rgy patriotic comedy showcase perfect for Independence Day weekend\nMultip
	le comedians delivering their best material about American life\nAn intima
	te club setting at one of Philadelphia’s premier comedy venues\nFull bar s
	ervice with cocktails\, beer\, and wine available\nA fun\, festive atmosph
	ere to celebrate the holiday weekend\nDoors open 1 hour before showtime — 
	arrive early for the best seats\n\nVenue Information\nPunch Line Philly is
	 Philadelphia’s premier stand-up comedy club\, located at 33 E. Laurel Str
	eet in the heart of the city. The intimate showroom offers excellent sight
	lines from every seat\, and the Callback Bar opens 1 hour before showtime 
	for pre-show drinks and mingling. Parking lots are available behind the ve
	nue at 49 Richmond Street and 1025 N. Front Street. \nTicket Information\n
	Tickets for 50 First Jokes About America at Punch Line Philly are availabl
	e now. Resale tickets start at $44. There is an 8-ticket limit per person.
	 Tickets are non-refundable unless the event is cancelled or postponed. \n
