	inks. We may earn a commission at no extra cost to you. \nAbout the Perfor
	mer\nBenji Brown is an urban comedian setting a new standard in comedy. He
	 toured with Martin Lawrence’s 2018 LIT AF Tour and is now the host of Mar
	tin Lawrence’s “Yall Know What It Is Tour.” His viral character KiKi has g
	arnered over 3 million views\, cementing him as one of the next major urba
	n comedic household names. \nEvent Details\nDate: Friday\, July 3\, 2026 \
	nTime: 9:45 PM (Late Show) \nVenue: Arlington Improv\, 309 Curtis Mathes W
	ay #147\, Arlington\, TX 76018 \nAge Restriction: 18+ \nPrice Range: $20 t
	o $60 per person \nAbout the Venue\nArlington Improv is located in the Hig
	hlands Shopping Center in Arlington\, TX\, across from Torchy’s Tacos. It 
	is an intimate comedy club featuring a full bar and restaurant where guest
	s enjoy world-renowned and local comics in a lively\, up-close setting. Th
	e venue also hosts Black Dog Pizza Arcade with 30+ local craft beers. \nWh
	at to Expect\nBenji Brown closes out Friday night at Arlington Improv with
	 a full late-show headlining set. Expect his signature urban humor\, chara
	cter work\, and high-energy delivery — the perfect late-night way to kick 
	off your 4th of July weekend. \nThis is an 18+ event. Food and beverage se
	rvice ends approximately 45 minutes into the show. All sales are final. \n
	Ticket Information\nTickets range from $20 to $60 per person. Purchase off
	icial tickets or find resale options below. \nOfficial TicketsResale Ticke
	ts\n\nhttps://comedycalendar.com/event/benji-brown-live-at-arlington-impro
	v-friday-late/\n\nFrom Comedy Calendar
